{"hits": {"hits": [{"created": "2026-01-30T19:56:56.948757+00:00", "modified": "2026-01-30T19:57:01.173697+00:00", "id": 18435764, "conceptrecid": "15257624", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.18435764", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.15257624", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18435764", "metadata": {"title": "Versioned Archive and Review of Biotic Interactions and Taxon Names Found within SternerLab/SternerLab-MammalVirusData hash://md5/db28aa6c428c598465e698eadb426110", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.18435764", "publication_date": "2026-01-28", "description": "Life on Earth is sustained by complex interactions between organisms and their environment. These biotic interactions can be captured in datasets and published digitally. We present a review and archiving process for such an openly accessible digital interactions dataset of known origin and discuss its outcome. The dataset under review, named SternerLab/SternerLab-MammalVirusData, has fingerprint hash://md5/db28aa6c428c598465e698eadb426110, is 11.2MiB in size and contains 7,360 interactions with 1 unique type of association (e.g., interactsWith) between 175 primary taxa (e.g., https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/ece3.10039) and 172 associated taxa (e.g., Mull, N., Schexnayder, A., Stolt, A., Sironen, T., &amp; Forbes, K. M. (2023). Effects of habitat management on rodent diversity, abundance, and virus infection dynamics. Ecology and evolution, 13(4), e10039. https://doi.org/10.1002/ece3.10039). This report includes detailed summaries of interaction data, a taxonomic review from multiple catalogs, and an archived version of the dataset from which the reviews are derived.", "access_right": "open", "creators": [{"name": "Elton", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Nomer", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Preston", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["biodiversity informatics", "ecology", "species interactions", "biotic interactions", "automated manuscripts", "taxonomic names", "taxonomic name alignment", "biology"],